	     Kano - Gunmen believed to be Fulani cattle herders killed 20 farmers praying inside a mosque over a land dispute in central Nigeria, a police spokesperson told AFP on Monday. The attackers opened fire inside a mosque in Etogi village during morning prayers on Saturday, Niger state police spokesman Bala Elkana said.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  